### Description

```ts
@Directive({
  selector: '[ngTemplateOutletWithInjector]',
})
export class WithInjectorDirective {
  constructor() {
    const outlet = inject(NgTemplateOutlet);
    outlet.ngTemplateOutletInjector = Injector.create({
      providers: [],
      parent: inject(Injector),
    });
  }
}

// The third-party component
@Component({
  selector: 'app-input',
  imports: [FormsModule],
  template: `
    <input [(ngModel)]="value" />
  `,
})
export class InputCmp {
  value = signal('');
}

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  imports: [
    ReactiveFormsModule,
    NgTemplateOutlet,
    InputCmp,
    WithInjectorDirective,
  ],
  template: `
    <ng-template #tmpl>
      <app-input />
    </ng-template>

    <div [formGroup]="form">
      <!-- <app-input /> -->
      <ng-template [ngTemplateOutlet]="tmpl" ngTemplateOutletWithInjector />
    </div>
  `,
})
export class App {
  form = new FormGroup({});
}
```

I have a third-party component that uses an `ngModel` directive inside it, and when I hardcode the component directly under a `div[formGroup]`, it renders correctly and everything works fine.

But when I render this template containing the third-party component under a `div[formGroup]` via `ngTemplateOutlet`, I create a `WithInjector` Directive to provide the "correct" injector, and it throws an `NG01350` exception.

The error message indicates that I should add `[ngModelOptions]="{standalone: ​​true}"`, but the problem is that it is a third-party component and I can't modify it directly.

I wonder how to provide the correct injector in this case to avoid `NG01350`? Many thanks :)

